&lt;h1 id=&quot;rotation&quot;&gt;Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h1&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rotation consists of 3 main combos:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Burst&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shroud&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Normal&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And should be looped in this order indefinitely.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Listed below are the combos:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Burst:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29855&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Nightfall (Greatsword 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10607&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Well of Darkness&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10546&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Well of Suffering&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62567&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Harbinger Shroud&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shroud:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62621&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dark Barrage (Shroud 2) x 2&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62563&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vital Draw (Shroud 5) when &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62621&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dark Barrage (Shroud 2) is almost ready&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62621&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dark Barrage (Shroud 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62540&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Exit Harbinger Shroud&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Normal:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30163&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gravedigger (Greatsword 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30860&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Death Spiral (Greatsword 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29740&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Grasping Darkness (Greatsword 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29705&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dusk Strike --&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30799&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fading Twilight --&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29867&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Chilling Scythe (Greatsword 1 Chain)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30163&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gravedigger (Greatsword 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will know when your auto attack chain is completed when the cooldown of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30163&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gravedigger (Greatsword 2) resets, in which case you should use it again immediately.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below 50% boss HP, you will notice that &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30163&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gravedigger (Greatsword 2) has no cooldown. Replace Greatsword 1 Chain with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30163&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gravedigger. Your &lt;strong&gt;Normal&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; combo will now look like this:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Normal:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30163&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gravedigger (Greatsword 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30860&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Death Spiral (Greatsword 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29740&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Grasping Darkness (Greatsword 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30163&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gravedigger (Greatsword 2) x 2&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you find yourself being forced out of Shroud early, just carry on and do your &lt;strong&gt;Normal&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; combo repeatedly until &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10607&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Well of Darkness is off cooldown, then recover and continue the rotation.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Becareful when using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10546&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Well of Suffering --&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62567&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Harbinger Shroud and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62621&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dark Barrage (Shroud 2) --&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62540&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Exit Harbinger Shroud, as casting either of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62567&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Harbinger Shroud or &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62540&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Exit Harbinger Shroud too early will cancel the skill before it.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This rotation will upkeep basically perfect &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100947&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of Fireworks uptime when performed correctly and up to speed. The skills that upkeep &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100947&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of Fireworks are &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29855&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Nightfall (Greatsword 4), &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29740&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Grasping Darkness (Greatsword 5), and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62563&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vital Draw (Shroud 5). You will notice that they are spaced out well throughout the rotation. Not having Alacrity will cause you to lose uptime on &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100947&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of Fireworks, but will not affect the order of the rotation.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;crowd-control&quot;&gt;Crowd Control&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your CC skills are:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shroud:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62540&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Exit Harbinger Shroud (Shroud 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62563&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vital Draw (Shroud 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Normal:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10647&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Charge&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62563&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vital Draw (Greatsword 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62540&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Exit Harbinger Shroud (Shroud 4) and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10647&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Charge are available during their respective stages for CC on demand. You can press them as soon as you see a breakbar appear with near 0 interruption to your rotation.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the other hand, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62563&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vital Draw (Shroud 5) and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62563&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vital Draw (Greatsword 5) are both used as part of your DPS rotation. They provide great CC when the breakbar coincides with your rotation phases, but you should not delay or save them for CC.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;advanced-tips&quot;&gt;Advanced Tips&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experienced players or players with lower ping might sometimes find that the &lt;strong&gt;Normal&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; rotation does not line up perfectly with the rest of the rotation, with some skills still being on cooldown when you reach that part of the rotation. To prevent this from happening, delay casting &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62563&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vital Draw (Shroud 5) --&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62621&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dark Barrage (Shroud 2) slightly longer, and your cooldowns should now line up. This problem can also happen if you delay &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62563&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vital Draw (Shroud 5) --&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62621&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dark Barrage (Shroud 2) by too much in one rotation, then too little in the next rotation.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
